## Project Structure

```
radical_semantic_compass/
│
├── config.py                 # all paths, model name, palette — edit here only
├── run_pipeline.py           # one-command runner with --step flag
├── app.py                    # Streamlit interactive demo
├── requirements.txt
│
└── src/
    ├── preprocess.py         # Excel → cleaned CSV
    │                         # auto-parses PairID structure, cleans Shuowen text
    ├── embed.py              # BGE encoding + PCA + saves embed_index.npz (768-dim)
    ├── analyze.py            # offset metrics, Rayleigh test, centroid stats, report
    ├── visualize.py          # scatter plot, polar rose, density map, ranking bar
    ├── radical_vectors.py    # 768-dim mean shift vectors per radical pair
    ├── phonetic_index.py     # inverted index: phonetic → radical → characters
    ├── predict.py            # three-case prediction logic + RadicalPredictor class
    └── llm_generate.py       # Qwen Plus prompt construction + API call
```

---

## Data Format

Input is an Excel file with one row per character. Characters sharing a phonetic component are grouped by a shared `PairID`. The two rows in each pair carry different radicals (currently 人部 and 心部).

| PairID | Character | Shuowen | Dazidian | Phonetic |
|--------|-----------|---------|----------|----------|
| 1 | 僮 | 未冠也。从人童聲… | 未成年的男子 | 童 |
| 1 | 憧 | 意不定也。从心童聲… | 意不定 | 童 |
| 2 | 仞 | 伸臂一尋，八尺… | 古代長度單位… | 刃 |
| 2 | 忍 | 能也。从心刃聲… | 忍耐；容忍 | 刃 |

**The `Phonetic` column is filled manually** — this is the only required manual annotation step. Automatic phonetic extraction from character forms is too error-prone for classical characters.

Text cleaning is fully automatic: `preprocess.py` extracts only the first clause from each Shuowen entry (the core gloss), stripping fanqie pronunciation notes, phonetic-semantic structural glosses, and Qing dynasty annotations.


---

## Key Design Decisions

**768-dim vs 2D for vector arithmetic.** All semantic offset computation happens in the original 768-dimensional BGE space. The 2D PCA projection is used only for visualization — it typically captures only 20–40% of variance, far too lossy for meaningful arithmetic.

**First-sentence extraction for Shuowen.** Shuowen entries follow a strict structural template: the core gloss comes first, followed by phonological analysis, classical quotations, and Qing dynasty critical annotations. Only the first clause is semantically relevant; the rest adds noise to embeddings.

**Embedding caching by text hash.** Re-encoding hundreds of classical Chinese entries with BGE takes several minutes. Cache files are named by MD5 of the input texts — if data hasn't changed, the embedding step is instant on subsequent runs.

**Rayleigh test for shift directionality.** The mean resultant length R measures whether shift vectors cluster in a consistent direction (R → 1) or scatter randomly (R → 0). A significant p-value means the radical has a stable, directional semantic function — which is the central empirical claim of this project and directly quantifiable for the thesis.

---

## Extending to More Radicals

The system generalizes to any number of radicals. To add 水部:

1. Add rows to your Excel with `Radical = 水部` and appropriate `PairID` groupings
2. Add `"水部": "#2ca02c"` to `RADICAL_PALETTE` in `config.py`
3. Re-run from `--step embed` onward

Shift vectors for all new radical pairs (人部→水部, 心部→水部, etc.) are computed automatically once there are enough paired examples.

---

## Tech Stack

| Component | Library |
|-----------|---------|
| Semantic embeddings | `sentence-transformers` · BAAI/bge-base-zh-v1.5 |
| Dimensionality reduction | `scikit-learn` PCA |
| Directional statistics | `scipy` Rayleigh test |
| LLM generation | Qwen Plus (OpenAI-compatible API) |
| Interactive visualization | `plotly` + `streamlit` |
| Static plots | `matplotlib` + `seaborn` |
| Label layout | `adjustText` |

---

## Background

This project sits at the intersection of **classical Chinese philology (古文字学)** and **computational linguistics**. The dataset draws from 《说文解字》 (Shuowen Jiezi, ~100 CE, the earliest systematic Chinese character lexicon) and the second edition of 《汉语大字典》.

The framing — that radicals encode a directional semantic function measurable as a vector offset — draws on work in distributional semantics on morphological analogies and linguistic feature vectors. The classical philological insight that 形声字 systematically encode meaning through their radical component maps naturally onto this framework.
